INUMBER 835
NAME 729
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
*DESCRIPTION_START
Its hair looks as soft as velvet and inviting to touch, though with the wary
look in its dark black eyes it might not be such a good idea. This spider
is quite large and probably capable of inflicting damage if did bite you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB PET -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The spider pushes affectionately against you hand as you pet it.
  ECHO OTHERS A large black tarantula pushes affectionately against %N's hand as %s pets it.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB HUG -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Using your thumb and index finger you give the tarantula a little hug.
  ECHO OTHERS A velvety tarantula wraps its legs around %N's wrist for a moment as it gives %N a little spider hug.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB KISS -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The tarantula taps your lips back with its two front legs in an attempt to give you a kiss back.
  ECHO OTHERS %n very gently kisses a black tarantula on its head and it instantly responds by tapping %N's lips with its two front legs.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The spider happily does 'push-ups' with all eight of its legs as you rub its back.
  ECHO OTHERS A large black tarantula does "push-ups' with all eight of its legs as %N gently rubs its back.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CARESS -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Immediately after you caress the hairy tarantula it runs up your arm and across your shoulder and snuggles up underneath your neck.
  ECHO OTHERS Immediately after %N caresses a hairy tarantula it runs up %N's arm, across %h shoulder and snuggles up under %N's neck.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB POKE -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The tarantula spins around twice after you poke it and looks at you warily.
  ECHO OTHERS %N pokes a large tarantula causing it to spin around twice on %N's arm and gaze at %i warily.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB KICK -1
IFVAR ITEMADJ3 = 566
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The tarantula leaps into the air, avoids your kick and then bites you on the leg!
  ECHO OTHERS As %N tries to kick a larage tarantula it leaps into the air avoiding %N's attack and then bites %i on the leg!
  SPELL 321 50
ENDIF
ENDIF
