NUMBER 3819
NAME Mort and Kain's House
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Fresh pine needles crunch softly underfoot as you enter this humble abode.
Long slender limbs, each one carefully stripped of its bark, have been smoothed
and polished and form the walls of this home. Soft moss has been stuffed
between all the cracks and crevices, shielding the interior from the elements
and making it snug and safe. A long hollow log, pushed through the ceiling,
acts as a vent for the stone ringed firepit. Thick comforters cover the
two cots near the back of the large room. A carved wooden table, much lower
to the ground than normal, has been placed between two huge pillows.
*DESCRIPTION_END
