INUMBER 1407
NAME 231
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
*DESCRIPTION_START
An example of exquisite craftsmanship, this small figurine is made from
gleaming white marble streaked with silver. So lifelike is the tiger one
can even make out the individual hairs in its thick coat. Its proud head
is held high with a fearsome look in its golden eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB RUB -1
  CLEARVERB
IFVAR ITEMVAL4 > 0
  ECHO PLAYER The tiger figurine glows momentarily as a flash of dazzling lights surrounds it, spreading outwards over the area.
  ECHO OTHERS A flash of dazzling lights suddenly fills the area.
  SPELL 230 50
  SUB ITEMVAL4 1
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB POKE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The tiger's eyes close slowly then reopen, glowing magically with a fierce protectiveness which gradually fades.
  ECHO OTHERS A dim light radiates from %N which gradually disappears.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TAP -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER A low gutteral roar emanates from the tiger figurine.
  ECHO OTHERS A faint roar suddenly comes from %N.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB THUMP -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The tiger figurine's haunches tense as the tip of its tail flicks back and forth!
  ECHO OTHERS You hear %N thumping on something.
ENDIF
;
